Our Management Team








Kent Kerbs
Kent serves as chief financial and administration officer of Sourcing Solutions, LLC. Kent joined Sourcing Solutions as an original team member. He has served as CFO since its inception in 2010. Kent is responsible for the company’s financial organization, the human resources function, and general administration duties.
Kent has over 20 years of accounting and finance experience and has worked with various leading companies in the finance industry. Prior to Sourcing Solutions, Kent served as Senior Manager at Capital Guardian Trust Company, one of the nation’s largest investment management organizations. Kent also worked as a Manager, Financial Reporting & Pricing for Pacific Investment Management Company, LLC (PIMCO). He is an alumnus of PriceWaterhouse and is a licensed CPA (inactive).
Kent received a BS in Business Administration with an emphasis in Accounting and Economics from the University of Kansas.









Lloyd Seeley
Lloyd serves as chief technology and operations officer of Sourcing Solutions, LLC. Lloyd joined the company as an original team member in 2010, and has more than 20 years of extensive hardware and software experience including planning, design and deployment of technical platforms, networking, product engineering, quality control, production management and operations.
Prior to joining Sourcing Solutions, Lloyd served as the owner and operator and consultant of a technical consulting firm to small and mid-sized businesses, where he streamlined processes in production, and operations by translating business needs with technology solutions. Lloyd also served as the MIS Director at the world’s leading independent distributor of data-center products. 
Lloyd‘s education and experience draws from advanced information technology training and hands-on experience.









Manny Garcia
Manny serves as the director of sales for end of life and refurbished products at Sourcing Solutions, LLC. Manny has more than 15 years of experience in the hardware industry and successfully runs a sales team known for fostering strong partnerships with suppliers, value-added resellers, purchasers and business partners. Manny’s team not only meets and exceeds established service-level agreements in sourcing response time, but is pivotal in keeping customers happy during the sales support process.
Prior to joining Sourcing Solutions, Manny served as Director of Channel Sales for Approved Memory where he provided legacy memory solutions to Fortune 1000 companies, focusing on fulfilling solutions that other large memory companies and OEM’s no longer support.









Chris Borghi
Chris serves as the director of category management and purchasing for Sourcing Solutions LLC, joining in April 2016. Chris has 15 years of experience selling and managing telecommunication equipment.
Prior to joining Sourcing Solutions, Borghi was the General Manager at Telogiks, LP in Irvine where he held responsibility for sales, inventory management, and remanufacturing. Previously he was VP – Telecom Equipment Division where he implemented a turn-around of their sales and profitability. Prior to that Chris spent 10 years at Paragon Communications with increasing sales roles and culminating in managing the Cisco product line. Chris will be responsible for streamlining the company’s purchasing processes and expanding the product management breadth and capabilities.
Chris Borghi earned his Bachelor’s degree from Boston College.









Kara Poovey
Kara serves as Manager for SSL, working with the leaders in the organization on strategic direction and community outreach. She seeks to continue Will's vision of a company that deeply values and empowers all team members and operates with Don Miguel Ruiz’s Four Agreements as central tenets:
 
Always do your best
Be impeccable with your word
Don't take anything personally
Don't make assumptions
 
Kara graduated from UCLA as a political science major, and began her career in corporate event planning for tech companies in Silicon Valley. She's currently involved in private equity projects that range from real estate development and urban renewal to agriculture and aerospace.









John Hyatt
John serves as general counsel and special assistant to the Manager.  He is responsible to provide executive oversight or perform duties as assigned.  He co-founded the company with William Poovey in 2010 and served as the company’s President until May 2014. 
John is also the managing partner of the law firm Einwechter & Hyatt where he focuses on assisting entrepreneurs and business owners. 
John graduated from the United States Military Academy at West Point, New York, (Dean’s List and Commandant’s List) in 1991.  He has over 26 years of active and reserve service in the U.S. Army and currently serves as the senior legal advisor to the Hawaii Army National Guard.  He graduated UC Hastings College of the Law (summa cum laude) in 1998.  












